?> 


after i tried and looked at the source code for the form Name, the tag <script> is disallowed.
whereas in the Message form the tag prefix which contains < is also not allowed.

it looks like the xss loophole is in the form name , becouse we can call javascript without using 
the tag <script> but the maxium input in the name form is only 10 characters. To overcome this we
can change maxlength is value by using the inspect element.

<td>
	<input name=txtName" type="text" size="30" maxlength="50">

input add : - 
name : 46465454446156446566546464
Message: Test

perform attack: - <body onload="alert(document.cookie)">

